history.text: Hello.  How are you today?
hey! Im good. Thanks and you
I am well,  Have you ever seen the movie Jaws?
Can you tell me more about the movie we need to discuss
I have when I was little
Absloutely.  It is about a large Great White shark who ends up off the coast in New England and he eats people.  :)
Made me scared to go swimming for a long time.  LOL.  It was Steven Spielberg's first big movie.
That definitely seems like I remember. I recall being scared
Great production and cast for the time it was filmed
great makeup and effects given the tech at the time
I have heard that the novel was very good, but I never read it.
Never read it either, did not know it was based on a novel.
There is this great scene where they think the first victim was killed by a boat but this shark hunter says "no and offers to get the shark for $10000.
The mayor wants to pretend nothing is happening.
Yeah I remember that scene. it was great.
I guess people want to deny what they cant control
It really is.  Robert Shaw who plays "Quint" the shark hunter is incredible.
You are right it is easier to deny that to accept.
Yeah, definitely one of the american classics
I really like the setting and the cinematography

There is another great scene where some fisherman claim to have found the shark--it is not the great white though.  Richard Dreyfuss is in it and he is the one who finds a shark tooth in the hull of another ship.
definitely deserved the oscars it got
Absolutely.  Still scary.
Yeah, I know, I dont know if I would do if I was close to a great white
Me niether.  The scene where Quint gets eaten by the shark is incredible.
Definitely, gore and suspense. Awesome!
and scary of course
He still tries to fight it.  How can you beat a Great White?
Definitely not by punching it
It is gory especially for a big film like that.  No.  Punching will not work.  LOL.
It was nice speaking to you today.
Same here, thanks!

uid1response.feedback: It was a really nice conversation

uid2response.feedback: He  was knowledgable about the movie
